title: Album Page, "Profile of Molding, Right Section of Pediment", late 19th century
medium: Graphite on off-white wove paper with deckled edge tipped into binding with fabric; verso: graphite, brush and gray wash.
markings: Watermark: Double inscribed circle containing an anchor, each terminal ending in an arrow.
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, right of drawing: right section of pediment / of Mich (?) / boths (?)
dimensions: Sheet: 30.9 x 21.2 cm (12 3/16 x 8 3/8 in.), irregular
description: Vertical sheet with a molding seen in profile that occupies two thirds of the page.
